Michael Niemira  , chief economist of
the New York-based International Council of Shopping Centers, 
says there is a trend toward "smaller footprints" for shopping 
centers. Niemira talks with Bloomberg's Ken Prewitt and Tom 
Keene on Bloomberg Radio's "Bloomberg Surveillance."     (Source: Bloomberg)  Running time 05:28
 